# CI Tools Package

## Purpose

`@dukkani/ci-tools` hosts internal CI automation and analysis commands (for example, workflow-failure analysis).

## Scope

- GitHub workflow/job log fetching and diff collection.
- Prompt construction and AI-powered incident analysis.
- Posting/updating PR comments with actionable summaries.

## Constraints

- This package is for CI/runtime automation, not application runtime imports.
- Keep external API interactions isolated and typed.
- Keep environment dependencies explicit through CI env presets.

## Security and Reliability

- Never log or expose secret tokens.
- Sanitize and truncate logs/diffs before sending to AI providers.
- Fail safely when data sources are unavailable; preserve useful diagnostics.

## Best Practices

- Keep command entrypoints small and orchestrate through focused modules.
- Keep GitHub API wrappers reusable and testable.
- Keep generated comments deterministic and easy for reviewers to scan.
